For those who are "afraid" of this app because location is turned on: Location has to be on because length of exposure is THE requirement of getting a notification. Passing by a device doesn't meet the criteria for exposure; you have to be within 6 feet of the other device for a period of time to trigger a notification. Also, you control what each app on your phone is able to do with the location setting within that app. Either yes, only when in use, or deny...it's not about "fear".
